+# Solution: ToQueryString with Table Valued Parameter is missing the type name
+
+## Root Cause
+
+In `SqlServerQueryStringFactory.cs`, two bugs combined to produce invalid SQL for Table Valued Parameters (TVPs) when calling `ToQueryString()`:
+
+1. **`TypeNameBuilder.CreateTypeName`** returned the literal string `"structured"` for `SqlDbType.Structured` parameters, instead of the user-supplied `TypeName` property (e.g. `"dbo.IntList"`).
+
+2. **`Create`** always emitted ` = ` followed by a value for every parameter, but TVPs in T-SQL `DECLARE` statements cannot be assigned a value — the correct syntax is just `DECLARE @p1 dbo.IntList;` with no assignment.
+
+Together, this produced:
+```sql
+DECLARE @p1 structured = ;
+```
+instead of:
+```sql
+DECLARE @p1 dbo.IntList;
+```
+
+## Change Description
+
+Two targeted edits to `src/EFCore.SqlServer/Query/Internal/SqlServerQueryStringFactory.cs`:
+
+1. **`TypeNameBuilder.CreateTypeName` (line ~194):** Changed the `SqlDbType.Structured` arm of the switch expression from `builder.Append("structured")` to `builder.Append(sqlParameter.TypeName)`, so the user-defined type name (e.g. `dbo.IntList`) is used.
+
+2. **`Create` method (lines ~50-82):** After appending the type name, added an `if`/`else` branch: for `SqlParameter { SqlDbType: SqlDbType.Structured }`, the ` = <value>` portion is skipped entirely (with an explanatory comment). All other parameters follow the existing path unchanged.
+
+## Files Edited
+
+- `src/EFCore.SqlServer/Query/Internal/SqlServerQueryStringFactory.cs`
+
+## Precedent Usage
+
+**Query:** `"ToQueryString Table Valued Parameter TVP structured type name SqlServer"`
+
+Result: one PR returned, score 0.421, marked `[BELOW THRESHOLD]` — it was about joining SQL Server TVFs (table-valued functions), unrelated to the `ToQueryString` bug. **Ignored — not useful.** The fix was implemented directly from the issue description, which pinpointed the exact lines to change.
